-- Ecuador Cerveceria Nacional Approves $94 Million Cash Dividend
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-03-27T17:52:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/ecuador-cerveceria-nacional-approves-94-million-cash-dividend.html
Shareholders of Cerveceria Nacional
CN SA, Ecuador’s biggest brewer, approved a $94 million cash
dividend, or $4.59 per share, for the 2011 earnings period.  The Guayaquil-based company, a unit of SABMiller Plc, has
already paid shareholder’s $2.60 per share and will distribute
the remaining $1.99 per share, it said in a statement published
today on the Quito securities exchange’s website. The company
did not say when it would make the additional payment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
